sured phase is\nalready known to a good approximation, or can be measured iteratively. As an\nexample, we calcu- late the phase-entanglement of the ground state of a\ntwo-well, coupled Bose-Einstein condensate, similar to recent experiments. This\nsystem demonstrates planar squeezing in both the attractive and repulsive\ninteraction regimes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2011 07:12:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 May 2012 07:28:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 14 Jun 2012 05:44:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-05-09"}
